<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4596033>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Habitus images of Pilophorus hyotan n. sp. (A–F) and P. typicus (G–I), live adult individuals. A. ♂. B. ♀. C. ♀, ventral view. D. ♀, ventral view. E. ♀, praying on an aphid. F. ♀, praying on a leafhopper nymph. G. ♂, from Kathmandu, Nepal. H. ♀, Surin, Thailand. I. ♀, Nagasaki, Japan, ventral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4596033/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4596041>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Habitus images of Pilophorus spp., live adult individuals. A–B. P. satoyamanus n. sp. ♂ (images courtesy of M. Takai). C–D. P. okamotoi ♂. E. P. setulosellus n. sp. ♀ (courtesy of M. Takai). F. P. setulosus ♀." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4596041/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4596065>
    dc:description "FIGURE 13. Male (A–B) and female (C–D) genitalia of Phelorepis hizenicus n. sp. A. Pygophore with parameres. B. Endosoma (vesica). C. Bursa copulatrix, dorsal view. D. Same, ventral view." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4596065/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4596083>
    dc:description "FIGURE 20. Scanning electron micrographs for Pilophorus niger (A–C), P. tagoi (D), and Pherolepis hizenicus n. sp. (E–O). A, D, G. Left lateral habitus. B, I. Metatarsus. Right lateral habitus. C, L. Endosoma. E. Dorsal habitus. F. Left-dorsolateral habitus. H. Thoracic pleura, left lateral view. J. Pygophore, dorsal view. K. Left paramere. M. Bursa copulatrix, dorsal view. N–O. Posterior wall of bursae." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4596083/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4596043>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Habitus images of conifer-inhabiting Pilophorus spp. (A–C) and Pherolepis spp. (D–H), live adults and 5th instar nymph (G). A. Pilophorus miyamotoi ♂. B. P. validicornis ♀ (image courtesy of M. Nozawa). C. P. tagoi ♀ (courtesy of M. Nozawa). D. Pherolepis hizenicus n. sp., ♂. E. Same, lateral view. F. Same, ♀. G. Same, 5th instar nymph, ♂. H. Pherolepis fasciatus ♀." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4596043/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4596037>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. Life cycle and immature stages of Pilophorus hyotan n. sp. (A–H) and P. typicus (I–J), laboratory observations in Nagasaki, Japan. A. Mating pair (♂ left). B. Eggs (exposed opercula) oviposited into border part between stem and root of Artemisia sp. C. First instar nymph, just after hatching. D. Same, before molting to 2nd instar. E. Second instar nymphs. F. Third instar nymph. G. Fourth instar nymph with 5th (left). H. Fifth instar nymph with its exuvia. I. Fourth instar nymph. J. Fifth instar nymph (feeding on brine-shrimp eggs) [MTNR = metanotal ridge]." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4596037/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4596049>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. A. Provisional result of molecular analysis for Pilophorus hyotan n. sp. and P. typicus (a-j in black and white circles showing sampling sites on cladogram). B. Distribution pattern of P. hyotan n. sp. and P. typicus in Nagasaki City area, SW Japan (numbers in square brackets corresponding to those mentioned in material examined section of respective species)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4596049/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

